            <p>Mercury, the innermost planet of the solar system and the eighth in size and mass. Its closeness to the Sun and
                 its smallness make it the most elusive of the planets visible to the unaided eye. Because its rising or setting is always
                  within about two hours of the Sun’s, it is never observable when the sky is fully dark. Mercury is designated by the symbol ☿. 
                Mercury is the closest planet to the Sun, at a distance of 57.91 million kilometers / 35.98 miles or 0.4 AU away.
                 It takes sunlight 3.2 minutes to travel from the Sun to Mercury.</p>
            
